----- stdout -----
Set commands will replace one segment of semver, with a specified one, and print out the mutated version

Usage: sem-tool set [OPTIONS] <SEMANTIC_VERSION>

Arguments:
  <SEMANTIC_VERSION>  

Options:
      --set-major <SET_MAJOR>
          
      --set-minor <SET_MINOR>
          
      --set-patch <SET_PATCH>
          
      --set-pre-release <SET_PRE_RELEASE>
          
      --set-build-metadata <SET_BUILD_METADATA>
          
      --mcp
          Run an MCP server over stdio that exposes this CLI's clap schema
      --mcp-http <ADDR>
          Run an MCP server over Streamable HTTP at ADDR (e.g. 127.0.0.1:8080)
      --export-skills <DIR>
          Generate Agent Skills (SKILL.md) from tools, resources, and prompts, then exit
  -h, --help
          Print help

